 in Arraiolos in 1892, worked as a seamstress and posed only with her face, although the representation of the Republic followed the style of bare shoulders com.mon at the time. Inspired by the classical image of Liberty, the bust was placed in the Constitu.ent Assembly in 1911. Ilda lived until 1993. Today, the bust is in the Museum of the Presidency of the Republic.\rFrance: Marianne, a woman wearing a Phrygian cap, symbolizes the republican values of �Liberty, Equality, and Fraternity�.\rBrazil: Inspired by Marianne, the effigy of the Republic appears on banknotes and coins, so.lidifying during the Republic and still present on Real currency today.\rArgentina: The Effigy of Liberty, created in 1881 by Eug�ne Oudin�, is represented by a wom.an wearing a Phrygian cap, present on Argentine coins.\r\r\rRobin Hood\rRobin Hood (conhecido em Portugal como Robin dos Bosques) � um her�i m�tico ingl�s que su.postamente viveu no s�culo XII, durante o reinado de Ricardo Cora��o de Le�o e as Cruzadas. Robin, um arqueiro habilidoso, morava na floresta de Sherwood e era ajudado por um grupo de amigos, incluindo Jo�o Pequeno, Frei Tuck, Allan Dale e Will Scarlet. Era famoso por roubar aos ricos para dar aos pobres, sendo considerado um s�mbolo de justi�a e liberdade. \rA hist�ria de Robin Hood, com origem incerta, foi difundida inicialmente atrav�s de baladas medievais e depois liter�riamente por autores como Howard Pyle, que enriqueceu a lenda com novos detalhes e personagens. Escritores como Walter Scott e Alexandre Dumas tamb�m con.tribu�ram para a imortaliza��o de Robin Hood na literatura. A lenda continua viva em Nottin.gham, com festivais, est�tuas e locais hist�ricos associados ao her�i.\rRobin Hood\rRobin Hood (known in Portugal as Robin dos Bosques) is a mythical English hero who supposed.ly lived in the 12th century, during the reign of Richard the Lionheart and the Crusades. Robin, a skilled archer, lived in Sherwood Forest and was helped by a group of friends, includ